 <H1>Alternatives for Data Entry k* in Index</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Three alternatives:
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI> Data record with key value k
<LI> <k, rid of data record with search key value k>
<LI> <k, list of rids of data records with search key k>
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Choice of alternative for data entries is orthogonal to the indexing technique used to locate data entries with a given key value k.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Examples of indexing techniques: B+ trees, hash-based structures
<LI>Typically, index contains auxiliary information that directs searches to the desired data entries</UL></UL></P>

